Description: Foot and stem sherd of Attic black-glazed pottery Vicup; foot in two degrees; tooled grooves (reserved) above and below fillet at junction of stem and foot; glazed black on exterior and underside; reserved: outer face of foot, resting surface and interior of stem inscription cut on underside.
Bibliographic references: Gardner 1888 / Naukratis II (p. 67, no. 870, pl. XXII, no. 870)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1655)
